        <num>CC 594</num>
        <heading>594.  Court costs; expenses of litigation</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 594.  Court costs; expenses of litigation
Court costs in actions concerning the property subject to the usufruct are taxed in accordance with the rules of the Code of Civil Procedure.  Expenses of litigation other than court costs are apportioned between usufructuaries and naked owners in accordance with the following Articles.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=110786</p>
        </authorialNote>
